      title: 'Larache Cemetery, Larache, Morocco',
      excerpt: 'cemetery',
      description:
        '            <p><b>Summary:</b> <p>Larache Cemetery in Larache (العرايش), Morocco.</p></p>            <p><p>Hidden away behind towering and beautiful white walls lies the Jewish Cemetery of Larache. The Argentinean writer Roberto Arlt once visited this site during a tour of North Africa, describing it as positively somber in comparison with Larache&rsquo;s Muslim cemetery, where he saw orange trees growing among the tombs.</p></p>            <p><b>Sources:</b></br>  No sources have been provided. </p>            <p><font color="#999999">© Digital Heritage Mapping, Inc.</font></p>',
