      title: 'Asilah Cemetery, Asilah, Morocco',
      excerpt: 'cemetery',
      description:
        '            <p><b>Summary:</b> <p>Assilah Cemetery in Assilah (أصيلة, Asilah), Morocco.</p></p>            <p><p>With shards and tiles scattered on the beach, and weeds slowly beginning to overtake the site, it almost seems like this seaside cemetery is slowly disappearing into the ocean. Somewhat overgrown now, it remains an inspiring as when, in the late 1970s, Moroccan author Edmond Amran El Maleh-Safi visited. He credits the trip with sparking his first novel, Parcours Immobile.</p></p>            <p><b>Sources:</b></br>  No sources have been provided. </p>            <p><font color="#999999">© Digital Heritage Mapping, Inc.</font></p>',
