      title: 'Synagogue at Amzrou, Morocco',
      excerpt: 'synagogue',
      description:
        '            <p><b>Summary:</b> <p>In Amzrou, a town in the Moroccan Sahara , even the Hebrew sign marking its synagogue has been lost.</p></p>            <p><p><strong>Interview:</strong> An old Muslim artisan, who learned his craft from Jewish inhabitants who once lived in Amzrou. Today the Jewish community has disappeared, but the old man still recalls the prayers of his teachers and colleagues.</p><p><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/VTk88g0f38o" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>Amzrou Man Recalls Jews\' Prayers</strong></em>&nbsp;</p><p>Only the mellah and synagogue building remains. Speaking in the Moroccan Arabic dialect of Darija, he recites some of prayers.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>            <p><b>Sources:</b></br>  No sources have been provided. </p>            <p><font color="#999999">© Digital Heritage Mapping, Inc.</font></p>',
