      title: 'Shrine of Raphael HaCohen at Achbarou, Morocco ',
      excerpt: 'shrinetomb',
      description:
        '            <p><b>Summary:</b> <p>Raphy Elmaleh takes viewers on a tour inside the shrine of Raphael HaCohen, a legendary rabbi who by tradition is buried in the village of Achbarou, south of Marrakesh.</p></p>            <p><p>Elmaleh interviews the Muslim caretaker of the tomb complex, shares the story of an old Jewish man who guarded the rabbi&rsquo;s grave for decades, and reveals his own mysterious encounter at the site.</p><p><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/1MjjZi50HQw" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>Shrine of Raphael HaCohen in Achbarou, Morocco&nbsp;</strong></em></p><p>The complex itself includes a synagogue, dining hall, guest rooms, well, and communal graveyard.</p></p>            <p><b>Sources:</b></br> <p>"Shrine of Raphael HaCohen in Achbarou, Morocco." Youtube video, 10:00, posted by "DiarnaInfo," June 9, 2010,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1MjjZi50HQw">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1MjjZi50HQw</a>.&nbsp;</p></p>            <p><font color="#999999">© Digital Heritage Mapping, Inc.</font></p>',
